results.name: Sum of divisors d of n such that n/d is not congruent to 0 mod 5.
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: G.f.: Sum_{k>=1} k*x^k*(1 + x^k + x^(2*k) + x^(3*k))/(1 - x^(5*k)). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Sep 12 2019
example: The divisors of 10 are 1, 2, 5, and 10. 10/1 == 0 (mod 5) and 10/2 == 0 (mod 5). Hence, a(10) = 5 + 10 = 15.
program: (PARI) a(n)=sumdiv(n, d, if(n/d%5, d, 0)); \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 20 2018
results.author: _Seiichi Manyama_, Apr 28 2017
